<br>
From this perspective, a dead class of any kind cannot sustain damage.  That goes for casters, and melees alike.<br>
<br>
So the argument that a caster needs to be balanced against a melee + healer is way off the mark.<br>
<br>
A melee class that doesn't take damage can sustain damage output indefinitely.  <br>
A caster class cannot.  (runs out of mana) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ushimone.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shimone</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 101<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/10/02 1:25 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re:</span><hr size=1> &lt;----doesn't need a healer to kill mobs.<br>
