<br>
Now in a group, when was the LAST time you ever heard of a Melee call for downtime because he was Forced into it through the game mechanics (Twink or Not doesn't matter).  The people that Manage the mana call the downtime, it's THEIR downtime that drags down the entire group.  When was the Last time you saw a Melee have to sit out a fight while everybody else does their Job?  Never seen it myself.  Yet I see Wizards sit out fights all the time(Myself Included) why?  Because for whatever reason we Burned all our mana in the prior fight.  Melee in a group has no downtime, whether that be Rogue, Warrior, Monk - the 3 Classes that have NO mana have no downtime in a group.  Any downtime there is imposed upon them BECAUSE of the casters running low on mana.<br>
