<br>
Seriously here, when you are in a group situation you need that tank as much as he need thats healer. You said it yourself in your post - &quot;Know how to avoid stealing aggro from tank&quot;. So basically in a group situation, you need more than that tank. Plus, if there is a warrior/paladin/sk in group you can bet that the rogue and monk are doing this famous &quot;non-healing damage&quot; too.<br>
<br>
And some people seriously under estimate tanks. At level 30 my Monk was in Cured Silk. Because of hunting in CC he gained enough money for Silver Chitin Handwraps and other nice goodies (on his own, I might add). By level 34 he could solo the whole Pit area, take care of the wanderers, and look for more waiting for the Pit area to respawn. He could do 2-3 fights before he would have to bandage up. Bandage trick + mend = 90+ health. Downtime = 1-2min. Rarely had to sit down and regain health ...just when adds came and FD failed more than once.<br>
<br>
I would like to see a Wizard do that. XP beat quading because downtime so small, fights were about 45 seconds each, and dungeon xp modifier on top of that.<br>
<br>
Be a level 30 something Wizard in EQ's present day with 'other's hits' turned on and embrace The Matrix. And no, I am no longer a level 30 Wizard but I do have a few alts and having knowledge of the Wizard class I know what we can and cannot do.<br>
<br>
Trust me, there is plenty of 'why'.<br>
<br>
<br>
