<br>
A warrior's ability to continue combat is based on how much damage he can withstand, a wizard's ability to continue combat is based on how much damage he can inflict.<br>
<br>
Where there is a will, there is a way.  Time and place.<br>
<br>
<br>
Editing this post because obviously alot of posts came in as I was posting mine, and Dryfft seems to be under the impression I have a reading problem.<br>
For clarity's sake, am I the only person that has Aggro kited and/or fear kited outdoors WITH a goddamn group?  YES, as a WIZARD I have been the factor that allowed a group to function OUTDOORS without a goddamn fucking asswipe healer.  Granted, the holy trinity is far easier, it is capable of getting the phat lewts and exploring the deep dungeons, but Wizards CAN and DO lend ALOT to groups and people whining and moaning about damage numbers and data crunching need to look at the big picture and get their heads out of their asses, or start a monk/rogue and shut up.  Slowly, Wizard DPS is being given enhancements, I for one have faith that Planes of Power WILL address alot of these concerns appropriately.  For now I am content in AOE groups, raiding, and OUTDOOR grouping on my horse with Mana Robe, familiar, Focus Items, KEI, PoTG, and any other mana regenerating effect I can cultivate.  Oh, critical strikes own. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uravilicuslolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ravilicus LoLF</A> at: 4/10/02 12:20:41 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udryfft.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dryfft</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 253<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/10/02 1:42 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re:</span><hr size=1> Ravilicus,<br>
