<br>
It seems a lot of people's comparisons are made with a monk with a fungi tunic.  A fungi tunic is rare to say the least.  I will probably never have enough pp to even think of buying one.  So while that is an example, it's not really enough to be a basis for comparison.  And even if wizards were made to be as powerful as a twinked tank, than we're putting all the people who are new to the game (ie, un-twinked) and play a tank at a disadvantage.  Now they need to be twinked to keep up with the casters.<br>
<br>
I'm not saying we don't need balance, but some people seem to be really irrational when discussing this.  The fact that we can deal out damage so fast DOES make a difference.  The fact that we can root and/or attack from a distance without taking any hits does make a difference.<br>
<br>
Think about it.  If a wizard could put out as much sustained damage as a tank (or tank with healer), and solo well, and quad kite, and port, and bind, why would anyone play a tank?  We would just have groups of 6 wizards all rooting and nuking.  There are other factors aside from sustained damage that need to be considered.<br>
<br>
On a side note, I have played two characters into their 30's, a shadow night and a wizard.  I have not noticed much, if any, difference in the availability of groups. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usaradin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saradin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 1649<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/10/02 2:06 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re:</span><hr size=1> But just to answer soloing since so many Wizards do it...<br>
