<br>
A twink... well let us not even go there. Let's just say all the manastones, horses, siw, etc. still will not keep you in the running. Not when they are taking on reds in LOIO and other places regening with their fungi tunics and wielding some pretty damn fun toys themselves.<br>
<br>
Post-50 the gap closes quite a bit. But SKs, Paladins even (mostly in undead places), Rangers, and most definately Monks will give Wizards a good run for their money in low 50s. At around level 60, good gear, maybe aaxp (depending on class) a melee will either match or regain the lead.<br>
<br>
SKs, Paladins, and Monks are awesome dungeon soloers - which means... dungeon xp modifier. Just by level 40 my Paladin friend was doing anywhere from 600-900dmg in procs <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> alone</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> against the undead - in a grouping situation making the fights last oh... 10-20 seconds. So even Paladins can solo quite well... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/urhiandedanaan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rhian Dedanaan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/10/02 2:10 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re:</span><hr size=1> You want to avoid the monk in a fungi?  Ok.<br>
<br>
I have a level 45 bard.  His gear is hardly uber - heck, I don't have complete lambent on him, I own one peice of singing steel (boots, Lev effect) and I'm wearing Mithril pants and a Sarnak Emblazoned Tabard.  Weaps are a Symphonic Saber and a D'Zok Wristsnapper.<br>
<br>
At level 45, I'm having trouble with my favorite soloing spot - because of all the competition with the 50 to 55 druids and wizards.  What's that again?  I'm soloing him in spots where casters five to ten levels higher are getting xp.  And while the bard isn't quadding, he doesn't have downtime either.  (In case you're wondering, I'm fearkiting at the Combine fort in DL.)  The songs I twist are Snare, Fear, and Haste songs.  When the mob turns into a runner I drop Fearsong and twist in Healing, and am full health before the fight is done.  Please note here - NO damage songs, all damage is melee.<br>
<br>
So, if you think wizards are balanced - or any casters for that matter - then tell me how a barely-twinked bard can nonstop kill blue through yellow mobs with no downtime while wizards and druids kiting four at a time have to stop and rest in between.<br>
<br>
Note, also, that this is in a soloing situation.  If you want to talk about grouping, ask yourself what a bard brings to a group vs. a wizard.  Ok, now stop laughing.  You KNOW the bard isnt' AFK for more than two minutes, tops, any zone I have any business fighting in at all.<br>
<br>
Yes, bards are generalists while wizards are specialists.  I still claim the comparison is valid, as I'm talking about all casters, not just wizards - and Druids have the same problems grouping that we do.<br>
